ly ensconced. What might one discuss with him? That article on Faraday in an old issue of Die Natur? No, that wouldn’t do. When he returned Serafim was standing by the bookshelf, examining the tattered, miserable-looking volumes.

“Stupid situation,” said Lev. “It’s really frustrating. Forgive me, for heaven’s sake. Maybe …”

(Maybe the water was just about to boil? No. Barely tepid.)

“Nonsense. To be frank, I’m not a great lover of tea. You read a lot, don’t you?”

